  "17": "  Do not rejoice when your enemy falls,\n  And do not let your heart be glad when he stumbles;\n",
✓ Proverbs 24:17
Fetching Proverbs 24:18...
  "18": "  Or the Lord will see it and be displeased,\n  And turn His anger away from him.\n",
✓ Proverbs 24:18
Fetching Proverbs 24:19...
  "19": "  Do not fret because of evildoers\n  Or be envious of the wicked;\n",
✓ Proverbs 24:19
Fetching Proverbs 24:20...
  "20": "  For there will be no future for the evil man;\n  The lamp of the wicked will be put out.\n",
✓ Proverbs 24:20
Fetching Proverbs 24:21...
  "21": "  My son, fear the Lord and the king;\n  Do not associate with those who are given to change,\n",
✓ Proverbs 24:21
